						<summary>

						<p>On four stone beams in the ceiling of the temple known as Nelaguḍi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged writing with no beginning and end on four beams seems to contain an eulogy of a person called Madhusūdhan of the Kasyapa-gotra and Karnāṭā-vamśa.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
